%html{ :xmlns => "http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml", :lang => "en", "xml:lang" => "en"}
  %head
    %title jQuery Placeholder Plugin
    %meta{"http-equiv" => "Content-Type", :content => "text/html; charset=utf-8"}
    %meta{:name => "description", :content => "jQuery plugin that adds support for the placeholder attribute in all browsers"}
    %meta{:name => "author", :content => "Andrew Jones, http://andrew-jones.com"}
    /[if lt IE 9]
      %script{:type => "text/javascript", :src  => "http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"}
    %link{:rel => "stylesheet", :href => "bootstrap.min.css", :type => "text/css"}
    %link{:rel => "stylesheet", :href => "index.css", :type => "text/css"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript", :src  => "http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.4.4.min.js"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript", :src  => "jquery.placeholder.js"}
    %link{:rel => "stylesheet", :href => "jquery.placeholder.css", :type => "text/css"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript", :src  => "http://google-code-prettify.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/src/prettify.js"}
    %link{:rel => "stylesheet", :href => "http://google-code-prettify.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/src/prettify.css", :type => "text/css"}
    :javascript
        jQuery(document).ready(function($) {
            try {
                prettyPrint();
            } catch(err) {}
            
            $(":input[placeholder]").placeholder();
        });
  %body
    :plain
      <a href="http://github.com/andrewrjones/jquery-placeholder-plugin/"><img style="position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; border: 0;" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_green_007200.png" alt="Fork me on GitHub" /></a>
    %div{:class => "container"}
      %div{:class => "content"}
        %div{:class => "page-header"}
          %h1 jQuery Placeholder Plugin
        %div{:class => "row"}
          %div{:class => "span10"}
            %p
              This is a simple plugin for
              %a{:href => "http://jquery.com", :title => "jQuery"} jQuery 
              that provides support for the
              %a{:href => "http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/Overview.html#the-placeholder-attribute", :title => "HTML5 placeholder"} HTML5 <code>placeholder</code>
              attribute in browsers that do not already support it.
            %p
              To use it, simply add the plugins CSS and JS files to the page and use the following JS to initialise it:
            %pre{:class => "prettyprint language-js"}
              :preserve
                jQuery(document).ready(function($) {
                  $(":input[placeholder]").placeholder();
                });
            %p
              Then in your HTML document, use the
              %code placeholder
              attribute with
              %code input
              tags. For example:
            %pre{:class => "prettyprint language-html"}
              :escaped
                <input type='text' placeholder='Some placeholding text' />
            %p
              If the browser already supports the
              %code placeholder
              attribute then the plugin will do nothing, unless you provide the
              %code overrideSupport
              option.
            %h2 Options
            %p
              The following options can be passed to the plugin.
            %h3 activeClass
            %p{:class => "option-description"}
              The class to apply when input is blurred. Defaults to
              %code placeholder
            %h3 focusClass
            %p{:class => "option-description"}
              The class to apply when input is active. Defaults to
              %code placeholderFocus
            %h3 overrideSupport
            %p{:class => "option-description"}
              Pass
              %code true
              to force the plugin to work on browsers which natively support the
              %code placeholder
              attribute. Defaults to
              %code false
            %h3 preventRefreshIssues
            %p{:class => "option-description"}
              Optionally attempt to prevent Firefox from auto filling values on refresh, by turning
              %code autocomplete
              off. Defaults to
              %code true
            %h2 Using With Autofocus
            %p
              If you want the field to autofocus when the browser loads, you need to ensure that you apply the placeholder first, as follows:
              :plain
                <pre class="prettyprint language-js">// apply placeholders - must be applied first before any autofocus actions
                $(":input[placeholder]").placeholder();
                // focus on the first text input field in the first field on the page
                $("input[type='text']:first", document.forms[0]).focus().select();
                </pre>
              Thanks to
              %a{:href => "https://github.com/hostdude99", :title => "hostdude99"} hostdude99
              for the hint.
            %h2 The Code
            %p
              You can download the source code from
              %a{:href => "http://github.com/andrewrjones/jquery-placeholder-plugin/downloads", :title => "downloads"} GitHub
              or go to the plugins
              %a{:href => "http://andrew-jones.com/jquery-placeholder-plugin", :title => "jQuery Placeholder Plugin"} homepage
              for more information
            %h2 Support
            %p
              Please use the
              %a{:href => "http://github.com/andrewrjones/jquery-placeholder-plugin/issues", :title => "issues" } GitHub issues tracker
              for any bugs or issues.
            %h2 Acknowledgements
            %p
              Thanks to
              %a{:href => "http://mal.co.nz", :title => "Mal Curtis" } Mal Curtis
              for many bug fixes and enhancements. Has probably writting more of the code than I have ;-)
